  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "The scheduler knows which pods are on which nodes. It figures out all volumes on a node by the sum of its pods.  It does this to enforce constraints in a cloud environment.\n\nIt is possible to delete a PVC while a pod is still running.  The pod will continue to function, the PV remains attached to a node.  \n\nWhen the scheduler attempts to place new pods on the node, it looks up all its existing PVs and their backing PVCs , except the PVC has been deleted, an error is thrown, and the scheduler fails.\n\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/plugin/pkg/scheduler/algorithm/predicates/predicates.go#L157\n\nThe user gets an ugly error message about a namespace they don't own. Their pod won't run and the error message is confusing.\n\n@kubernetes/rh-storage @kubernetes/sig-storage \n",
  "closed_at": "2018-01-08T10:31:55Z",
